attributes.name: namespace
attributes.description:
Namespace defines the space within which each name must be unique.
An empty namespace is equivalent to the "default" namespace, but "default" is the canonical representation.
Not all objects are required to be scoped to a namespace - the value of this field for those objects will be empty.

Must be a DNS_LABEL. Cannot be updated.

attributes.name: app.kubernetes.io/instance
attributes.description: A unique name identifying the instance of an application.

attributes.name: app.kubernetes.io/version
attributes.description: The current version of the application (e.g., a SemVer 1.0, revision hash, etc.).

attributes.name: app.kubernetes.io/part-of
attributes.description: The name of a higher level application this one is part of.

attributes.name: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by
attributes.description: The tool being used to manage the operation of an application.
